      <lg type="edition">
<l>īyeṉa viratta liḻintaṉ ṟataṉeti</l>
<l>rīyē ṉeṉṟa lataṉiṉu miḻintaṉṟu</l>
<l>koḷḷeṉak koṭutta luyarntaṉ ṟataṉetir</l>
<l>koḷḷē ṉeṉṟa lataṉiṉu muyarntaṉṟu</l>
<l>teṇṇīr parappi ṉimiḻtiraip peruṅkaṭa</l>
<l>luṇṇā rākupa nīrvēṭ ṭōrē</l>
<l>yāyu māvuñ ceṉṟuṇak kalaṅkic</l>
<l>cēṟoṭu paṭṭa ciṟumait tāyiṉu</l>
<l>muṇṇīr maruṅki ṉatarpala vākum</l>
<l>puḷḷum poḻutum paḻitta lallatai</l>
<l>yuḷḷic ceṉṟōrp paḻiyala rataṉāṟ</l>
<l>pulavēṉ vāḻiya rōri vicumpiṟ</l>
<l>karuvi vāṉam pōla</l>
<l>varaiyātu curakkum vaḷḷiyōy niṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Begging while saying “give” is lowly. Against that, (1)</l>
<l>saying “I won’t give” is more lowly than that. (2)</l>
<l>Giving while saying “take” is lofty. Against that, (3)</l>
<l>saying “I won’t take” is more lofty than that. (4)</l>
<l>Those who want water will not be ones who drink (6)</l>
<l>from the large sea with roaring waves, with an expanse of clear water. (5)</l>
<l>Even though it is stirred up when cows and deer go [and] drink, (7)</l>
<l>[and] of low quality as it occurs with mire, (8)</l>
<l>there are roads many at the side of drinking water. (9)</l>
<l>Apart from blaming bird [omens] and times, (10)</l>
<l>those who go, remembering, are not not blame. Therefore, (11)</l>
<l>I won’t be vexed with you, may you prosper, Ōri, (12a-c+14d)</l>
<l>you generous one who gives without limit, (14a-c)</l>
<l>like the clouds in a mass in the sky. (12d-13)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
